node.text:
Harmony is more achievable than balance. You can’t have every aspect of your life divided into equal parts (balance). With harmony, things ebb and flow together. 

#nedranuggets

node.title: The Difference Between Balance and Harmony

ACT is a therapeutic modality is used with individuals and couples. The process is intended to help you become more of yourself by becoming more flexible in your thinking and being.

In this conversation, we cover:
What is estrangement
How to reconcile
Keys times when people disconnect from family
How politics impact family relationships 
And more 

Shirt by @heytiffanyroe 

Guest @pillemer 

#nedranuggets 
#setboundariesfindpeace

Sometimes we don't have an explanation for saying no, quilting, or not liking something. 

It's okay to trust your gut and do what's best for you.

Be assertive as a way to protect your mental health.

node.text:
People may not get it the first time. Give them time to adjust to your boundaries. If they aren't adjusting after some time (you determine the time frame), consider what needs to change about how you implemented the boundary.

Are you honoring your boundaries with others by holding them accountable? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I don't know who needs to hear this, but: The adults were supposed to protect you; you weren't supposed to protect yourself. It's not a child's job to take care of themselves emotionally, physically, or otherwise. @NEDRATAWWAE WW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Kids are NEVER mature enough to take care of themselves. They need support from caregivers. 

#nedranuggets

node.text:
A MANTRA FOR CYCLEBREAKERS 

A cycle breaker is a person who is breaking a generational pattern or any unhealthy pattern in their life. 

Your cycle might look like unhealthy relationship habits, people-pleasing, being the first in your family to attend college, etc. It's your choice to choose how you want to live. 

#nedranuggets #cyclebreakers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Hopefully, one day you'll get tired enough to stop: @NEDRATAWWAB giving your energy to dysfunctional relationships trying to prove a point to a person who isn't listening forgiving the same person for the same thing over and over trying to trust untrustworthy people putting on a happy face when you aren't okay allowing people to convince you that it's your fault when they hurt you pretending that keeping the peace (staying quiet) is helpful for your mental and emotional health www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
Sometimes, it takes time to get to a point where you no longer tolerate others' unhealthy behaviors.  
When you reach your breaking point, try not to judge yourself for staying too long in an unhealthy situation. You likely left when you were tired enough and ready. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on August 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Forced apologies are not apologies; they are indications of guilt, people-pleasing, and shame. Let's practice apologizing when you mean it and intend to do better (for real). You can say, "I feel bad about what I did." Instead of issuing apologies without depth. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Apologizing is a choice, and when you choose to do so, be mindful and do so with the intention to do better. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'PLEASE STOPT @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
Small changes can positively impact your relationships.

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'PLEASE STOPT @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stop telling people not to cry when you can't handle their emotions. Crying can mean many things; perhaps talk to the person about what they're feeling instead of trying to get them to disconnect from their feelings. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stop guilt-tripping people when they say no. When you guilt-trip, you are creating an environment where honesty is not allowed. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stop yelling to get your point across. Speaking louder doesn't increase others' understanding, but it will make them more hesitant about listening to you. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Stop assuming you already know what someone will say, what they will do or who they are. Ask more questions and make fewer assumptions. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stop thinking that everyone else should think and feel like you. What we think and feel is based on our our life experiences and many other factors. We are not all the same. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'I'm still doing the work, so it's likely that: @NEDRATAWWAB I will make a mistake in my judgment my boundaries won't be crystal clear to others I will have an off day I won't handle bad news in the best way my emotions will impact my behavior I won't be able to explain what I'm feeling and why won't remember to use the appropriate coping skills I will forgive someone and later regret it won't be perfect www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
We are not complete; we are works in process and progress. 

If you don't always get it right, give yourself some grace. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'For peope who are stuck in relationships that no longer feel nourishing: Stop trying to force relationships with people just because you've known the person for a long time. History does not mean connection; history says that there' a shared past. It's okay to remember the past without forcing yourself to recreate moments with people who you no longer feel a real connection to or people you've outgrown. Reflect fondly without the guilt ofrecreating the past. People change. And sometimes they don't change. Some things (and people) are better left in the past. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
{Some relationships are not meant to last forever.}⁣
⁣
It’s okay to allow things to naturally evolve or dissolve. ⁣
⁣
#nedranuggets #cyclebreakers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Repeat After Me Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. Protecting my energy is my #1 priority. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Choose peace over people-pleasing. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Let's allow Simone Biles to be an outstanding example of practicing self-care. Taking time for your mental health is more important than forcing yourself to push through when your wellness is at stake. Mental health is a reason to take a day off. Mental health is a reason to step back from something. And mental health is a reason to say no. @NEDRATAWWAB WW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Protecting your mental health is a great way to practice self-care. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5 THINGS THAT IMPACT YOUR ABILITYTO EXCEL @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
You cannot stay the same and excel. You will have to change your thinking, your relationships, and more. 
 
Staying the same is not an option if you want something different. 
 
#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5 THINGS THAT IMPACT YOUR ABILITYTO EXCEL @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You may find it challenging to excel if you're surrounded by people who aren't in the same growth-oriented space as you. You don't have to let people go, but perhaps a little distance could help you go further. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You may find it challenging to excel if you're using your past as a reason not to perform presently. You can process your past while being focused on what you need to do now. Your past will be there, and you are defining your future choice by choice. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You may find it challenging to excel if you seek validation from people who don't understand you. What is good for you might not make sense to everyone. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You may find it challenging to excel if you compare yourself to people who have different resources than you. People have difficult strengths, and they are not all created equal. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says '@ You may find it challenging to excel if you're waiting for things to be perfectly aligned before getting started. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Growth is seeing your parents as humans outside of their role as your parents. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
People are people, even when those people are your parents. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Forgiveness is possible when you can understand the stories of others (without judgment) and acknowledge how what you experienced wasn't about who you were. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Forgiveness does not mean allowing unhealthy situations in your life. Forgiveness means allowing yourself to heal. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#nedranuggets⁣ #cyclebreakers ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 24, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stop trying to persuade people to stay in an unhealthy family relationship because you believe, "family is everything, no matter what." Without knowing what's truly best for someone, you might be advising people to stay in harmful, abusive, or intensely stressful situations. Encouraging people to push through impossible situations is not a healthy way to support them. Let's practice allowing people to do what's best for them even when you would personally do something different. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Sometimes what's best for someone is not what you would feel comfortable doing in your own life. Pushing people to be in situations that aren't healthy for them causes shame and impacts their mental health.

Its okay to not give advice when it not supportive. 

*The last sentence in this post can be applied to a variety of situations. “Let's practice allowing people to do what's best for them even when you would personally do something different.”

#nedranuggets
